POLOKWANE – Temperatures will remain in the low to high teens in the city this week. According to People’s Weather’s forecast, temperatures will range from 14ºC to 21ºC.  Monday to Wednesday will be cold with maximum temperatures at just 14ºC, while Thursday and Friday will be warmer at 16ºC and 18ºC, respectively. Partly cloudy conditions will persist throughout the week and there is a 10% chance of rain expected on Tuesday. The weekend will be warmer with sunny conditions expected. Saturday (July 2) will reach a high of 19ºC while Sunday will warm up to a mild 21ºC. 